#  ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†ò‚†Ñ‚£Ä‚°Ä‚†∏‚†ì‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚††‚†ü‚†ã‚†Å‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä                                              

===[ Time Series Analysis Summary ]=============================================
1|> Understand the data
    - What is a time series? A sequence of data points collected at regular time 
      intervals (daily sales, hourly temperature, yearly GDP).
    - key property: 'order matters' (yesterday's value influences today) 

2|> Explore the data (EDA) 
    . 'Visualize' Plot the series to see 'trend', 'seasonality', 'outliers'
    . 'Check stationarity': does the mean/variance stay constant over time?
      (Important for many models)
    . 'Decompose': Break the series into
      - 'Trend' (long-term direction)
      - 'Seasonality' (repeating cycles)
      - 'Noise/Residuals' (random variation) 

3|> Preprocess / Prepare
    - Hanlde 'missing values'
    - Remove outliers if necessary
    - Apply 'transformations' (log, differencing, scaling) to 'stabilize'
      'variance or achieve STATIONARITY' (feature scaling part) 

4|> Model the Series
    - Depending on the goal: 
      1|> Descriptive / Decomposition
          - 'Additive' or 'Multiplicative' models (Trend + Seasonality + Noise)
          - 'STL' decomposition
      2|> Classical Forecasting Models 
          - 'ARIMA / SARIMA' -> good for short-to-mid term forecasting
          - 'Exponential Smoothing (Holt-Winters)' 
            |-> captures trend + seasonality
      3|> Machine Learning / Deep Learning Models 
          - 'Tree-based models' (random Forest, XGBoost)
            |-> neet feature engineering (lags, rolling means).
          - 'Neural networks' (LSTM, GRU, Transformers) -> learn long-term
            dependencies. 

5|> Validate the Model 
    - Split data into 'trin/test sets' (time-based, not random) 
    - Use 'metrics' like:
      . 'MAE' (Mean Absolute Error)
      . 'RMSE' (Root Mean Squared Error)
      . 'MAPE' (Mean Absolute Percentage Error) 

6|> Forecast & interpret 
    - Generates forecsts for future time steps 
    - Always 'visualize predictions vs actuals' 
    - Interpret seasonality/trends to extract insights
      (e.g.. "sales peak every December")

7|> Iterate & Refine
    - Try different models 
    - Tune hyperparameters
    - Incorporate external features (holidays, weather, promotions) 

===[ Summary (shortcut view): ]===
- Visualize ‚Üí see trend/seasonality
- Check stationarity
- Decompose (trend + seasonality + noise)
- Model (ARIMA, SARIMA, Prophet, ML, DL)
- Validate with test data
- Forecast & interpret
================================================================================
